Dubai, 2 x Junior Architect Positions Working on Prestigious Project
Job currently available
Serial No: 5185
Location: Dubai, United Arab Emirates -
Once in a lifetime opportunity working on one of the modern wonders of the world the new Taj Mahal building in Dubai.
You will be working with internal and external architects and the client wants the freshness of youth and you will be a recent graduate with a maximum of 2 years experience.
These positions are for the highly creative who wish to express themselves and contribute to what will be a major global attraction
You will be required to carry out the following actions:
Go to www.skills-provision.com and register.
You can then upload your CV and create a personal profile.
You need to create a video off less than 3 minutes all about you and architecture and why you should get one of these jobs
You need to create a portfolio presentation that can be viewed without CAD equipment and sent it to enquiries@skillsprovision.co.uk
Rewards: US$40,000-US$50,000 tax free.
You will operate as part of an overall project team working closely with a range of professionals from quantity surveyors to building services engineers.
The emphasis of your work is the planning of the internal design of a 300 bed hotel and shopping plaza of the highest quality:
Creating designs and highly detailed drawings both by hand and by using specialist computer-aided design (CAD) applications.
Taking ideas from the owners and translating their vision into reality
Liaising with other professionals about the feasibility of a proposed designs, including constraining factors such as planning legislation, environmental impact and project budget.
Working closely with a team of other professionals such as building service engineers, construction managers, quantity surveyors and architectural technologists.
Writing and presenting reports, proposals, applications and contracts as required.
Determining the materials to be used and specifying the requirements for the project.
Adapting plans according to circumstances and resolving any related problems that may arise during construction.
Making sure the project is running according to schedule and budget.
Playing a part in project and team management.
Travelling regularly to building sites, proposed locations and client meetings.
Experience required:As above
Qualifications:Fully qualifed
Travel required:
No Transport provided:
No Required CRB:
No
